HEADWORD: Gyral
<hw>Gy"ral</hw> <pr>(j⟦imac⟧"r⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Gyre</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving in a circular path or way;
whirling; gyratory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to a gyrus, or
convolution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gyrant</ent>⟦br⟧
